<paragraph id="23D803ADF3EC4EDF7DA8EFDD487384D4" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A667A8B90119C28B61E1C2A1B316E0F" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName id="5867CD384CD37821F426501BBB553084" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Poecilma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poecilma papaveratum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveratum">
<emphasis id="5911AADDF92B1F4A657761BDD7D8899D" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Poecilma papaveratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Germar, 1824 [by original designation].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E739056855AFDA0CE2DB988E74C61A9E" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" type="gender">
<paragraph id="468094580214D14AF0DE72FA9B47B773" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Gender.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34630151A8A742625A3021BDDA502FA" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Masculine.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3BAFD12EEF7A0EC9E8D3276FFEC22C89" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E1ECE324CAFB341D479BB466CD462127" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6CE70629AD70BD631D1AAFE87D487EA3" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName id="8971169D4CE581A01FF8F6C26A7F3E27" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="653FF9F194693502B97F951236876FBD" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DA1BD32A3FC1492DECED4827ACEF65A2" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86623EFC1BAC6A7AA4BA73AF34BA6E2F" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a concealed scutellum and a closed receptacle of the mesoventrite that is laterally flanged near the apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E137AC9444516A4CB845DF731C1B9F7C" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 9. Variation in the mesoventrite. 1 Trichodocerus brevilineatus [ARTSYS 0000616] showing a prosternal rostral &quot; sheath &quot; with the sides converging below the procoxae, the transverse ridge anterior to the mesocoxae and the region of the mesoventrite posterior to the ridge with dense yellow scales 2 Lobops bonvouloiri [ARTSYS 0000527] showing a cup-shaped receptacle for receiving the rostrum 3 Piazurus trifoveatus [SSAC 0001118] with an &quot; open &quot; channel on the mesoventrite 4 Pseudopinarus condyliatus [SSAC 0001116] with an &quot; open &quot; channel on the mesoventrite 5 Acoptus suturalis [ASUHIC 0016914] showing a flat, unmodified mesoventrite 6 Copturus sanguinicollis [ASUHIC 0086638] showing a closed receptacle on the mesoventrite with lateral flanges 7 Cylindrocopturinus pictus [SSAC 0001288] showing a rostral channel of the mesoventrite formed by relatively parallel carinae and no posterior termination 8 Euzurus ornativentris [ARTSYS 0000796] 9 Hoplocopturus javeti [SSAC 0001289] with an inverted U-shaped carina and the region posterior to the carina invaginated." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.683.12080.figures1–8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/143826" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">6</figureCitation>
), and can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="AFB37669281FA4BE548A8403710C2100" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22A8D2986CCA1C519E769FF6F6F8521B" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the ventrally toothed pro- and mesofemora, larger tarsal claws, and flattened (not costate) elytral intervals. The first two funicular articles vary in length among the species, with the second article being longer than or subequal to the first (
<bibRefCitation id="B1BA325EC547DB61D4F15E67952AB2A5" author="Champion, GC" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="52" pageNumber="103" refId="B20" refString="Champion, GC, 1906b. Insecta - Coleoptera - Rhychophora - Curculionidae - Curculioninae (part). In: Champion GC (Ed.) Biologia Centrali-Americana (Vol. 4, part 5). 1-136." title="Insecta - Coleoptera - Rhychophora - Curculionidae - Curculioninae (part). In: Champion GC (Ed.) Biologia Centrali-Americana (Vol. 4, part 5). 1 - 136." year="1906 b">Champion 1906b</bibRefCitation>
: 87).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B161805D505263A49B489A3EA8157CD" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2BD5F692EAF52F1DCCBEFEB583DE10B9" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96EEE01C7C391732E800E84BC23C8CC5" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">
The usage of this generic epithet has a particularly complicated history, as explained by 
<bibRefCitation id="B87E859CB75EEBE8E69E853011FFF785" author="Muniz-Velez, R" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Mexicana (NS)" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="249 - 258" refId="B119" refString="Muniz-Velez, R, Ordonez-Resendiz, MM, 2010. Una especie nueva de Macrocopturus Heller (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Conoderinae) de Guerrero, Mexico y descripcion de sus estados immaduros. Acta Zoologica Mexicana (NS) 26 (2): 249 - 258" title="Una especie nueva de Macrocopturus Heller (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Conoderinae) de Guerrero, Mexico y descripcion de sus estados immaduros." volume="26" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="4BEC088616BCE56611EBF0A905007E82" originalValue="Muñiz-Vélez">Muniz-Velez</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="98CC94652ED67D8E4C699DEC91A23144" originalValue="Ordóñez-Reséndiz">Ordonez-Resendiz</normalizedToken>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. The first usage of the name 
<taxonomicName id="963D46CE9FDCF31450CD7A5BA196ADF3" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E861225206DAD9F09D59744AEF11D08D" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="2945E662C603EB70A79B0A971EC6B8F6" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zygops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygops" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EF4013ABF82D9FFBB6F71B86A319DBDA" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Zygops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A67113DF6977E201AA521C27ABC397AD" author="Schoenherr, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Environmental Entomology" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" refId="B139" refString="Schoenherr, CJ, 1825. Tabulae synopticae familiae curculionidum. Isis Oken, heft V, columns 581-588." title="Tabulae synopticae familiae curculionidum. Isis Oken, heft V, columns 581 - 588." year="1825">Schoenherr 1825</bibRefCitation>
: col. 586), where the type species was designated as 
<taxonomicName id="2A380DB8237EC9D43ED253B688468578" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Poecilma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poecilma papaveratum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveratum">
<emphasis id="5E72FE9C0CB196A25CF8418BF299E09E" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Poecilma papaveratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Germar, 1824. The subgenus was elevated to genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="A9AD55BC30169E6DDE8A66FB3D279E40" author="Dejean, PFMA" journalOrPublisher="errata, unnumbered]" pageId="53" pageNumber="104" refId="B33" refString="Dejean, PFMA, 1835. Catalogue de la collection de Coleopteres de M. le Baron Dejean (edn 2). Part 4, Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, 257-360." title="Catalogue de la collection de Coleopteres de M. le Baron Dejean (edn 2). Part 4, Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, 257 - 360." year="1835">Dejean (1835)</bibRefCitation>
, and dozens of additional species were described to the genus (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E21F63BE28F6D2A834DA5BCA1DBB3CE" author="Schoenherr, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Environmental Entomology" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" refId="B143" refString="Schoenherr, CJ, 1838. Genera et species Curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. Leonardo Gyllenhal, C.H. Boheman, et entomologis aliis illustratae. Paris, Roret; Lipsiae, Fleischer. Vol.4(2): 601-1121. [+ pp. 1122-1124 (Corrigenda)]" title="Genera et species Curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. Leonardo Gyllenhal, C. H. Boheman, et entomologis aliis illustratae. Paris, Roret; Lipsiae, Fleischer. Vol. 4 (2): 601 - 1121. [+ pp. 1122 - 1124 (Corrigenda)]" year="1838">Schoenherr 1838</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A20D504D88A555BBC4150D0883ECAA63" author="Schoenherr, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Environmental Entomology" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" refId="B144" refString="Schoenherr, CJ, 1845. Genera et species Curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. Leonardo Gyllenhal, C.H. Boheman, et entomologis aliis ilustratae. Paris, Roret; Lipsiae, Fleischer. Vol.8(2): 1-504." title="Genera et species Curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. Leonardo Gyllenhal, C. H. Boheman, et entomologis aliis ilustratae. Paris, Roret; Lipsiae, Fleischer. Vol. 8 (2): 1 - 504." year="1845">1845</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5D97FE840BDD9C068E3E64DCB41D8C8B" author="Kirsch," journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="56" pageNumber="107" pagination="161 - 208" refId="B93" refString="Kirsch, , 1875a. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift: Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 19 (1): 161 - 208" title="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift: Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt." volume="19" year="1875 a">Kirsch 1875a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BD275B20EB769F0E030D1F5563D36DDD" author="Kirsch," journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="56" pageNumber="107" pagination="241 - 304" refId="B94" refString="Kirsch, , 1875b. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift: Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 19 (2): 241 - 304" title="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift: Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt." volume="19" year="1875 b">b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="38005F0686BD1954B2201515F598A179" author="Heller, KM" journalOrPublisher="University of Washington Publications in Biology" pageId="54" pageNumber="105" refId="B56" refString="Heller, KM, 1895. Zygopiden-Studien II, mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der Gattung Copturus. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koeniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Etnographischen Museums zu Dresden 1894/95 (11): 1-70." title="Zygopiden-Studien II, mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der Gattung Copturus. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koeniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Etnographischen Museums zu Dresden 1894 / 95 (11): 1 - 70." year="1895">Heller (1895)</bibRefCitation>
created several genera out of specimens included in 
<taxonomicName id="BAE23CAE7A4FFFB20E986C9BE6DCFBDF" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6D56571035DB5BB0D0CF7C184A591CE0" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AC6CB9062A6D35D4EE076AD421E4510B" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="95AA422D8AD995DDC8FAE0EA867B2739" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Heller, 1895 for the species of 
<taxonomicName id="6B745B8B40FF5AD57AF45C8E6E907988" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5055732521B873E1603E4D811A1CE548" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="72">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that have a concealed scutellum, second funicular 
<pageBreakToken id="21E46782DCAD8D22F005530FFF148180" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" start="start">article</pageBreakToken>
that is barely longer than the first, and a unique, horseshoe-shaped modification to the mesoventrite. Among the species moved from 
<taxonomicName id="70EBDC8CDB9832AAF663D5E7360FCE16" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FA782FAC0844718C04362895A0D3FBC9" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into 
<taxonomicName id="039AD4584CA0E1311DD71468C4A2D71E" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="941D6535BFEBB77A81781C69D706E3C9" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<taxonomicName id="8492139D5EE057405A860548CBB1545F" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Poecilma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poecilma papaveratum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveratum">
<emphasis id="7D17208EB78F73877E5545754EC16F2F" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Poecilma papaveratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which Heller recognized as the previously designated type species of 
<taxonomicName id="3BEBB2F0642CEFB9E5A3495F070763B9" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2272B19BE6A78A8AEE3CA477AC31F34D" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E3E8B87D2DDE5FA04A4109F6A5300FEE" authority="O'Brien &amp; Wibmer, 1982" authorityName="O'Brien &amp; Wibmer" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Neozurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neozurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="817A4A785BBFFA153F998066F1CD230E" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Neozurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="23D102608BC9C0215E3673689CBBE51C" originalValue="O’Brien">O'Brien</normalizedToken>
&amp; Wibmer, 1982 was created as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="4587F3FA396B2DE014B46777867E691D" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BC25151EFD7DF2CD70885B2BE6752EC" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="48BA8D6F634A7B53C99FE1EC893BA73F" author="O'Brien, CW" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="57" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 382" refId="B122" refString="O'Brien, CW, Wibmer, GJ, 1982. Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of North America, Central America, and the West Indies (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 34: 1 - 382" title="Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of North America, Central America, and the West Indies (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="34" year="1982">
<normalizedToken id="CE1519A9A89B8809A288D46C1EE17789" originalValue="O’Brien">O'Brien</normalizedToken>
and Wibmer 1982
</bibRefCitation>
: 4) which was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="2165C2368D515B09053C2ECC98194D89" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD1BCE2B21E1C05D6708C36E26C298A" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Amyot, 1846 and was later synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="D28E8B5BC81B4D3674DA30461018B063" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5ADDC92986E4EE85FD1D556E03A4ABF9" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an unjustified replacement name (
<bibRefCitation id="BC79E55AF88ECADF1CFB8123AB7E3EE8" author="Wibmer, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 563" refId="B153" refString="Wibmer, GJ, O'Brien, CW, 1986. Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number 39: 1 - 563" title="Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="39" year="1986">
Wibmer and 
<normalizedToken id="040DAC30D7A95D2D9CEFCA5C3E4BAB30" originalValue="O’Brien">O'Brien</normalizedToken>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B2A61A7D826ABA400F8BAB14A60F1785" author="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA" journalOrPublisher="Entomopraxis, Barcelona" pageId="51" pageNumber="102" refId="B1" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA, Lyal, CHC, 1999. A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Entomopraxis, Barcelona" title="A world catalogue of families and genera of Curculionoidea (Insecta: Coleoptera) (excepting Scolytidae and Platypodidae)." year="1999">Alonso-Zarazaga and Lyal 1999</bibRefCitation>
: 111). As a result, all species treated as 
<taxonomicName id="6E2E425AD8938AE7088501D92A98A49E" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBB2973D9CDE11DBE1CE6BFB681A6EE6" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Heller became newly recombined as 
<taxonomicName id="D97744BDC0BE15D3BC977501E6407CAC" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Meliaceae" genus="Macrocopturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrocopturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D445AC7F2F0FFA6CD800A0B3E8DE9ED7" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Macrocopturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of 
<normalizedToken id="9115168337B6A6AE4E88BD1909F00F99" originalValue="Heller’s">Heller's</normalizedToken>
original subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="5B6958EA724658EF18A684160CA53082" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0E47FBDB6B2AEB1ACF60A9225E37ACC" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
elevated to genus (
<bibRefCitation id="F0F102685FB07E028D1516EE074867D9" author="Wibmer, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 563" refId="B153" refString="Wibmer, GJ, O'Brien, CW, 1986. Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number 39: 1 - 563" title="Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="39" year="1986">
Wibmer and 
<normalizedToken id="9316FB79AEA811049C9BECB85E81BF04" originalValue="O’Brien">O'Brien</normalizedToken>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
: 17), and all species treated as 
<taxonomicName id="01703765BC40B70176112CEABEC799B7" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CD1CDE660939BB19A2C53BC55C041234" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Heller and subsequent authors until 
<bibRefCitation id="EA85C406C748DF56378A1FAD1B4BA98C" author="Wibmer, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number" pageId="58" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 563" refId="B153" refString="Wibmer, GJ, O'Brien, CW, 1986. Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute Number 39: 1 - 563" title="Annotated checklist of the weevils (Curculionidae sensu lato) of South America (Coleoptera: Curculionidae)." volume="39" year="1986">
Wibmer and 
<normalizedToken id="94F0015F9CF52BD5486EC4DA967419DD" originalValue="O’Brien">O'Brien</normalizedToken>
(1986)
</bibRefCitation>
became newly recombined as 
<taxonomicName id="A49B99D0EF708B8C7F8F33AAB71C3039" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22A7F240970C64B4F53F91790E909582" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, returning the type species 
<taxonomicName id="4472B5EAC69558ED281AA66C86A193EA" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Poecilma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poecilma papaveratum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papaveratum">
<emphasis id="6236AC7EF2B71133287D48368A3036A2" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Poecilma papaveratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to its original genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4044B3812295E6E3471D0D9D1EBD5A65" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" type="key">
<paragraph id="B2494301E34C9080B242CE0A3BCB9FAE" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="45EC39CF2290893B128575470ECE05FB" genus="Keys" lsidName="Keys" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" rank="genus">Keys</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="902FE690FFE0D51FCC7F09E6C1A14F81" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">
Champion 1906: 87 (to 
<taxonomicName id="07BE12D8043DC3CA891CE94B3ACEDB75" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6CE5E32B9F8239EA8E41715B27709DF" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Central America), 
<bibRefCitation id="7B6612C7630179EDF77130786E922B84" author="Heller, KM" journalOrPublisher="University of Washington Publications in Biology" pageId="54" pageNumber="105" refId="B56" refString="Heller, KM, 1895. Zygopiden-Studien II, mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der Gattung Copturus. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koeniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Etnographischen Museums zu Dresden 1894/95 (11): 1-70." title="Zygopiden-Studien II, mit besonderer Beruecksichtigung der Gattung Copturus. Abhandlungen und Berichte des Koeniglichen Zoologischen und Anthropologisch-Etnographischen Museums zu Dresden 1894 / 95 (11): 1 - 70." year="1895">Heller 1895</bibRefCitation>
: 5 (to 
<taxonomicName id="636D9A4F40A147590DA8465D508E81A7" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Zurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9666D03E7DF132FE5B84EB4F334C0315" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Zurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Central and South America).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84FD1BA9C3C91974114C878162760F58" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" type="phylogenetic relationships">
<paragraph id="2F2F0C04776265F8610CCC27DB8EA127" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Phylogenetic relationships.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E8EF484E114BD8794E577A683A39DE1" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">
<bibRefCitation id="AF259604CDB03CA12CDC3A0260ECB2A6" author="Hespenheide, HA" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterists Bulletin" pageId="55" pageNumber="106" pagination="313 - 321" refId="B63" refString="Hespenheide, HA, 1984. New Neotropical species of putative ant-mimicking weevils (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Zygopinae). The Coleopterists Bulletin 38 (4): 313 - 321" title="New Neotropical species of putative ant-mimicking weevils (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Zygopinae)." volume="38" year="1984">Hespenheide (1984</bibRefCitation>
: 315) suggests a relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="B9EEA191FA8A7DA595E0AC60867F49E5" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="865A7EE6D2758FDD43C7DE5F02811CB6" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ECEB852BB9B43828BFC70111FC57B0A8" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Euzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="64C0A2DD3985D4E09F5A26E8B3E5D052" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Euzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6BC046DF3B1E4BAE3F5DFCD71BBCABDF" authorityName="Sleeper" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Santalaceae" genus="Cylindrocopturinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindrocopturinus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90FC127EA788B18685FA1DD54B143DE7" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Cylindrocopturinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of those three, it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0683D1D1D0C3B4F36FD3661EC064E875" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BA65F938F5F1E5C2E5CCD1AE6EC025EF" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only differences given by Champion (1906: 87) being the ventrally toothed pro- and mesofemora, the larger body size and comparatively proportionate tarsal claws. 
<taxonomicName id="7D79AE93026B8AFC31AEEFED2B03FB4B" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Euzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCB2740F4BCB20BB9BC068706DF24ACF" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Euzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a scutellum concealed by a posterior lobe of the pronotum, but the manner of 
<normalizedToken id="3A9C85CF9AFD248F606A0560E8725C7A" originalValue="it’s">it's</normalizedToken>
concealment differs from 
<taxonomicName id="9E2811FF403614E84CD2D8E0EA6507E6" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CC494CCB1D09663531534A19B72D2F87" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="370ECFE516BA05154408EB909C86E08F" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A43C6C60CBD1B8800BD30D28FC5FF56" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: where the posterior pronotal lobe of 
<taxonomicName id="1C2417C53A300E73906C3B80E0938492" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="43A443D502ED6B3043511DF4D38F6165" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5A959107DCA46A1F239D5CD4951C16B0" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB5C8EEB5D332765AE1B6E913F5FC8AD" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subducts the elytra, completely concealing the scutellum, in 
<taxonomicName id="7649135D7923FCAB4FABB06F57CDD2EF" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Euzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D30399704F6D854EB8F2FD369B16D59B" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Euzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the posterior lobe is only extended posteriorly and not below the elytral base, leaving the scutellum visible in posterior view. Despite this difference, Lyal et al. report Type II sclerolepidia to be present in 
<taxonomicName id="2030D7348C529BA4CC0BB1302E903051" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="926C6F6B5023F3B47C996A06022B9C2D" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="406C917098F57D4A7F19FA754BDF382E" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B27C1604CA6EF14B3CA445698BEB1685" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73CF7CD755461D7DFBED031802A6322C" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Euzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0BE7EEEE45771FF53232F4F7AEE1B935" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Euzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which, among the sclerolepidia-bearing lechriopines, is only also known in the very different 
<taxonomicName id="3839DADDF42BDC564485438E380C1111" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Oleaceae" genus="Psomus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psomus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9EBD1AC8BFE8E3A604B7BD52ED2603BB" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Psomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See entry on 
<taxonomicName id="F7DDF4C22BA64BF85893B0E0F3EB91FB" authorityName="Sleeper" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Santalaceae" genus="Cylindrocopturinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cylindrocopturinus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3E92B8323E3A4A88E6E6710A17E04F3" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Cylindrocopturinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the present interpretation of the relationship of that genus. The relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="EF731D23E0148C7E696B219C1AE4BCA8" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9E09475776554E88121F77FB278C2075" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8FD2A1803A0C362B33DD54FFDF4968D9" authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7B44A3E1BABBDDE6E85BF5331382EF25" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Microzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName id="0E0D005D72B0C0D5E25C160AC00BDA69" authority="Lacordaire, 1865" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lechriopini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lechriopini" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lechriopini</taxonomicName>
and whether or not 
<taxonomicName id="AEE97D3826D576B131213A9A236B0ECE" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Euzurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euzurus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="29EFE6AD8C6EB61C562F57C4CEF6121F" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Euzurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found to be the sister-genus is not easily hypothesized by the external characters examined thus far.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9787E30615D79C447C6EB7750BE1485" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" type="host">
<paragraph id="BDA8DE4E84F33D748782DC6F9EFB9815" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Host associations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="31DB9FA8BF61CF4194ECD4A88CFAC815" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">
The widespread Central and South American species 
<taxonomicName id="74BCEC9D5565B3F86E420ACE5682E5DE" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Copturus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Copturus aurivillianus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurivillianus">
<emphasis id="DF851E60E3F72B0F96C5A998D9399BD4" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Copturus aurivillianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Heller, 1895) is reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="15874B41D81D29C6596C57658F269D85" author="Costa-Lima, A da" journalOrPublisher="Serie Didatica" pageId="53" pageNumber="104" pagination="3 - 373" refId="B28" refString="Costa-Lima, A da, 1956. Insetos do Brasil. 10° Tomo, Coleopteros, 4.a e ultima parte. Escola Nacional de Agronomia. Serie Didatica 12: 3 - 373" title="Insetos do Brasil. 10 ° Tomo, Coleopteros, 4. a e ultima parte. Escola Nacional de Agronomia." volume="12" year="1956">Costa-Lima (1956</bibRefCitation>
: 219) to bore stems of 
<taxonomicName id="CC41037B123CD321018D7939A8C37058" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Canavalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Canavalia" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="26A6E1946F2AA1A66B8C08D285CD95E4" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Canavalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Adans., 
<taxonomicName id="839EB0A8414D1F27B3083B9BD55C374C" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dolichos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dolichos" order="Rosales" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6825E16C7089E6CE6F9E94141CC863CD" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Dolichos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., and 
<taxonomicName id="A0EC86AB0273D8AA1960448BBCDB3669" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Phaseolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phaseolus" order="Fabales" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="874EDC8669E6FE60BAFA3A7E0EF1D38F" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="73">Phaseolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="EEC4953C32334007343513646E92E59F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Phaseolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="22" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) as larvae in Brazil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
